note.ab:
In his letters Van Gogh repeatedly used the image of a worn-out cab-horse as a metaphor for the hard life of man in general and the artist in particular. See e.g. letters 148, 211, 599 and 611. In the Netherlands he had read the poetry of François Coppée, who had written a poem, ‘Cheval de Renfort’, about it (from the collection 
                            Le cahier rouge
                        ). See Coppée 1880, p. 163.
